Package: sriov-vfs
Version: @VERSION@
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Maintainer: schlarpc <schlarpc@gmail.com>
Depends: pve-manager, iproute2
Description: Mellanox SR-IOV VF provisioning for Proxmox VE
 Creates SR-IOV virtual functions on a Mellanox ConnectX NIC (switchdev mode
 with deterministic per-VF MACs) and registers them as Proxmox PCI resource
 mappings. The work is split across two correctly-ordered systemd units so the
 VF/representor setup runs before networking while the pvesh mapping sync runs
 after pmxcfs is available.
 .
 Configuration lives in /etc/default/sriov-vfs.
